.TH OLLAMA\-MCP 1 2025-06-01 ollama\-mcp-0.1.0
.SH NAME
ollama\-mcp \- MCP server exposing Ollama models as tools
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ollama\-mcp
.RB [ \-config
.IR path ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ollama\-mcp
is an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that exposes a local Ollama
language model as a tool over stdio.
An MCP host launches
.B ollama\-mcp
as a subprocess and communicates via JSON-RPC over stdin/stdout.
The host can then call several tools to run prompts or list models on the
configured Ollama model.
.PP
The data flow is:
.RS
MCP host \(<-stdio/JSON-RPC\(-> ollama\-mcp \(<-HTTP\(-> Ollama
.RE
.SS Tool: generate
Generate text using the configured Ollama model.
.TP
.B prompt
(string, required) \(em the prompt to send to the model.
.TP
.B system
(string, optional) \(em system message override.
.PP
The tool returns the complete generated text as MCP text content.
.SS Tool: chat
Multi-turn conversation with the configured Ollama model.
.TP
.B messages
(array of objects, required) \(em list of messages.
Each message object must have
.B role
(string) and
.B content
(string) fields.
.SS Tool: list_models
List available models in the Ollama instance.
Ollama errors are returned as tool-level errors so the MCP host can
handle them.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-config " path"
Path to the YAML configuration file.
Default:
.BR config.yaml .
.SH CONFIGURATION
The YAML config file controls the Ollama connection.
If the file is missing or values are unspecified, defaults are used.
Environment variables
.RB ( OLLAMA_HOST ,
.RB OLLAMA_PORT ,
.RB OLLAMA_MODEL ,
.RB OLLAMA_MAX_TOKENS )
override the configuration.
.TP
.BI host " hostname"
Ollama server hostname or base URL.
Default:
.BR localhost .
.TP
.BI port " number"
Ollama server port.
Default:
.BR 11434 .
.TP
.BI model " name"
Ollama model to use for generation.
Default:
.BR llama3 .
.TP
.BI max_tokens " number"
Maximum number of tokens to generate (maps to Ollama's num_predict).
Default:
.BR 1024 .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Clean shutdown.
.TP
.B 1
Fatal error during startup or operation (e.g.\& missing config, invalid
Ollama URL).
.SH EXAMPLES
Configure
.B ollama\-mcp
as an MCP server in Claude Desktop:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "ollama": {
      "command": "/usr/bin/ollama\-mcp",
      "args": ["\-config", "/etc/ollama\-mcp/config.yaml"]
    }
  }
}
.EE
.RE
.PP
Run with a custom config:
.PP
.RS
.EX
ollama\-mcp \-config /path/to/config.yaml
.EE
.RE
